{"text": "After playing this game for a good amount of time and still getting whopped in multi, I must say this is still one of the best fighting games I've ever played. Though I wasn't very big when it came to fighting games, this in particular encoraged me to be involved with the genre even more. To get into detail, Skullgirls is a solid recommendation that cannot be ignored. The controls are clean and responsive, and the combos are enjoyable to pull off. The music is great, the animations are beyond fantastic for a 2D fighter, and there are 9 base characters (5 in DLC) each lovable with their own unique playstyle and backstories. If you aren't the type who plays online multi and just like to solo, the storymode is also enjoyable. If you are a beginner who wants to play online, the tutorial gets you comfortable with the game pretty quickly and the online itself has nearly no issues. So whether you are new to the fighting genre or have experience, this game covers just about any skill level. Overall, for a fighting game that's only $10, Skullgirls will not dissapoint you. The 2nd Encore Upgrade is also a good deal if you plan on investing more time into the game. The DLC adds more characters, trials to learn more advanced combos, and a fully voiced storymode for all your favorite characters.", "appid": "245170", "steamid": "profiles/76561198272081719", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1534420800.0}
