{"text": "Very fun game, you should enjoy the beautiful learning curve for a while. There is an element of grind in this game but I simply find it necessary at first sight Most of the time, when we grind in this game we have a goal, a weapon we wish to craft which makes us stronger or a warframe or mod(enchantments/upgrades, etc.), however once you get the hang of it and made a few warframes and made them strong enough, you will began to lack challange. Getting into conclave is bulls hit because there is no one there, the game lacks pvp-players, at the very most you can convince people to join pvp and that's about it, no one likes pvp in this game, they think its for satisfying egos. As for the beatufiul slashing and killings, at some point you begin to one shot everything and increase level to make things the same difficulty again, so the game really doesn't change in that regard which is a disgrace to ones' intelligence. Level 1 guy killing level 1 dragon with level 1 sword, level 99 guy killing with a different sword and different warframe a level 99 slighlty different dragon. Mostly the game becomes this way if you manage to make the connection between the sentences I just described. So I suggest you to quit the game when it gets repetitive because why repeat? You are an intelligent person who looks for new challenges, who will only bear repetitive tasks for the sake of a very rewarding, unique item. Once the game platau's stop it when it's fun and you will leave with wonderful memories. I suggest quitting around mastery rank 4 and leave with good memories instead of making a strong character which doesnt even translate to pvp lol.", "appid": "230410", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113643295", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1582027200.0}
