{"text": "I will start by saying that this game is my favourite and the best game i've ever played in my life. Its a masterpiece but its far from perfection... There isnt a perfect game but The Witcher 3 its the only one that comes close to it. (IMO OFC) Graphics: The graphics are amazing, of course you need a great graphic card to experience the game to its fullest, but an decent gpu will do it for you without taking that breathtacking moments away. The nature, the mesmerizing landscapes, the monsters, the castels, the cities, the villages, the fights and so â™¥â™¥â™¥â™¥ much more... ITS ALL AMAZING! And on the DLC Blood and Wine that happens in Toussaint omfg... its so gorgeous. I couldn't stop taking screenshoots. Well enough talk lets rate. Rate- 9/10 Original Soundtrack: Without a doubt one of my favourite OST's ever. There wasn't a moment in the game where i felt tired of the music. Marcin PrzybyÅ‚owicz did an amazing job! The music was always engaging, made the battles sound more epic and ''hardcore''. Rate- 9/10 Combat: The combat system changed so much since the first ''The Witcher''. I hated the combat system in the first one but this one? I love it! Its so fluid, it works so well with all the ''spells'' you have. Its one of my favourite combat systems, but it has some flaws, some times Geralt doesnt do what i tell him to do and one of the biggest problems is when you dont want to fight or you want to run cuz the enemy its to high lvl, because of the ''enemy lock'' its hard to run from a fight you dont want to take... But well the fights are amazing, the finishers moves and the combos are awesome and great to look at. It make us think that we are better than we really are. Rate- 8/10 Quests: Dude you will never run out of quests... you always have some Witcher contracts quest some where on the billboard, and even if you only do the main quests, the game is long af. Almost every single main quest has different choices that you can make that will influence the end of the game. You have the main quests ofc, a great amount of side quests, a countless number of Witcher contracts, and also some fun treasure hunt quests. (150 hrs and im not even close to finish the game 100%). Rate- 10/10 The narrative/plot/history: This is the reason why we all love The Witcher,the opportunity to become a BADASS monster hunter, that uses swords and magic? Pliz thats ma dream right there. But for real tho, the plot is amazing, im a fan of the books, and even tho the games aren't cannon, its still amazing, the opportunity to become Geralt, follow him throw this amazing world, with different types of enemys, great characters that make you care about them even if they are not main characters, the kingdoms, the empire, EVERYTHING ITS AWESOME AND INTERESTING! It's like you are playing BADASS and handsome character in a more interesting version of Game of Thrones. Well i could talk alot more about the plot and how amazing it is... believe me, its like playing a book or a tv series, and better yet, you are the one that makes the choices that leads to an amazing ending no matter what ending it is. (Forgot to say that the line between comedy and serious scenes is amazing, this games has alot of harsh moments, romance, drama, comedy and all of that is well balanced) Rate- 10/10 (I wish i could give it more than 10/10) GWENT: Dude YOU HAVE A FREACKING CARD GAME INSIDE THE GAME! I love Gwent (even tho i hated it in the first 2 games), you can buy cards to make you deck better, you can play with alot of NPC's, you can earn money buy betting that you will win, there are alot of decks that you can build. Its like having Heartstone inside World of Warcraft. Rate- 9/10 DLC's: Ma man let me tell you, you cant get better for a better price. Each DLC its almost like a full game. The game is already a masterpiece and good but with both DLC's???? MAAAAAA MAN!!!!! Both DLC's are worth buying, IMO the best DLC's ever created, even tho Hearts of Stone its kinda good and has an interesting story, Blood and Wine IT'S THE BEST DLC EVER PERIOD. Blood and Wine is double the length the Hearts of Stone, you go to Toussaint wich is an gorgeous area, with the best landscapes in the game, the story is also amazing and thrilling And the best part?????? Both DLC's are cheaper than any AAA game in the market, you can get The Witcher 3 + DLC's cheaper than a AAA game on steam sales, and let me tell you, IT WILL BE THE BEST WELL SPENT MONEY ON YOUR LIFE! (Oh and btw you have plenty of free DLC's too.) Hearts of Stone- 9/10 Blood and Wine- 10/10 Now i want to thank to CD Projekt RED for doing this amazing job, it was an long and awesome journey guys, since The Witcher 1 to the 3 it was an gigantic progress, and the decision of delaying the game so you guys could polish and refine was well worth it! Thank you guys! I cant wait for Cyberpunk 2077! Well guys, im sorry if i made alot of grammar mistakes but im not that great at grammar so sorry :S", "appid": "292030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198029596974", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466337600.0}
