{"text": "Originally when I found this game I was browing the steam store in one of those dazes where one is bored and none of the owned games were really tempting.  That's when I found this (though I installed it then didn't touch it for a week).  Initially when I started playing it I had very low expectations and wasn't even sure if I wanted to get \"into\" it but what REALLY caught my attention was the opening, which in turn made me keep play it instead of giving into my assumptions. I adored the art work throughout the entirety of the game and the music was to die for (literally?). Then the story came, oh boy did it come with a bittersweet taste. Without spoiling it I will say it started out rather optimistic I think. Of course you get the feeling that something is wrong you still have a little hope to find what you're looking for, but then it hits you. Once it does the story gets progressively darker until the very end until you see what really happened. That's when the anger hits!  There were some technical difficulties (only one or two) so definitely mega WORTH to play the game. Also, who doesn't love a good puzzle game? So why not try it? It's free and there's two \"chapters\". Give it a whirl! 10/10 have made friends play.", "appid": "465520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198101349819", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1474718400.0}
